# ✅ (a) Equivalence Class Design

Equivalence Class Partitioning ka matlab hota hai input ko groups (classes) mein divide karna — valid aur invalid.

### 1. Age (18 to 60)

* Valid Class:

  * 18 ≤ age ≤ 60
* Invalid Classes:

  * age < 18
  * age > 60

👉 Classes:

* EC1: age < 18 (Invalid)
* EC2: 18–60 (Valid)
* EC3: age > 60 (Invalid)

---

### 2. CGPA (0.0 to 10.0)

* Valid:

  * 0.0 ≤ CGPA ≤ 10.0
* Invalid:

  * CGPA < 0.0
  * CGPA > 10.0

👉 Classes:

* EC4: CGPA < 0 (Invalid)
* EC5: 0–10 (Valid)
* EC6: CGPA > 10 (Invalid)

---

### 3. Credits (12 to 30)

* Valid:

  * 12 ≤ credits ≤ 30
* Invalid:

  * credits < 12
  * credits > 30

👉 Classes:

* EC7: credits < 12 (Invalid)
* EC8: 12–30 (Valid)
* EC9: credits > 30 (Invalid)

---

### 4. Semester (1 to 8)

* Valid:

  * 1 ≤ semester ≤ 8
* Invalid:

  * semester < 1
  * semester > 8

👉 Classes:

* EC10: semester < 1 (Invalid)
* EC11: 1–8 (Valid)
* EC12: semester > 8 (Invalid)

