# ✅ (c) ECP vs Boundary Value Testing

### 🔹 Equivalence Class Partitioning (ECP)

* Input ko groups/classes mein divide karta hai
* Har class se ek test case lete hain
* Focus: **general behavior**

👉 Example:

* Age valid class = 18–60 → ek value test karna enough

---

### 🔹 Boundary Value Testing (BVA)

* Sirf edge values test karta hai
* Focus: **limits pe error pakadna**

👉 Example (Age):

* 17 ❌
* 18 ✅
* 60 ✅
* 61 ❌

---

### 🔥 Simple Comparison Table

| Feature         | ECP              | BVA                |
| --------------- | ---------------- | ------------------ |
| Focus           | Classes (groups) | Boundaries (edges) |
| Test Cases      | Kam              | Thode zyada        |
| Error Detection | General          | Edge cases         |
| Example         | Age 25           | Age 17,18,60,61    |

---

# 🧠 Final Simple Line (Exam ke liye)

👉 ECP inputs ko groups mein divide karta hai, jabki BVA sirf boundary values test karta hai jahan error hone ke chances sabse zyada hote hain.

